text:
The org.apache.tomcat.modules.SimpleSessionStore class seems to be a bit too 
aggressive in re-using ServerSession instances.  In particular it seems to want 
to use the same instance for different session-Ids.  Needless to say, this 
opens a major security problem when one person's info gets sent to someone else.
I would recommend:
diff -c SimpleSessionStore.java.orig SimpleSessionStore.java
*** SimpleSessionStore.java.orig        Mon Feb 26 14:59:53 2001
--- SimpleSessionStore.java     Mon Feb 26 14:48:42 2001
***************
*** 426,432 ****
        if (session == null) {
            session = new ServerSession();
            session.setManager( this );
!           recycled.put( session );
        }

        // XXX can return MessageBytes !!!
--- 426,432 ----
        if (session == null) {
            session = new ServerSession();
            session.setManager( this );
! //        recycled.put( session );
        }

        // XXX can return MessageBytes !!!
